s the phase where most of the teenagers start taking decisions about their future study choices and any study experience at school help them in making these decisions such resolutions in teenage can have impact on their future practical lives finally those youngsters who are bullied during their teenhood at school can suffer from personality disorder later in their lives which can have detrimental affect on their future surely these experiences in teenage can affect a child s future to conclude i believe that both pre school childhood and teenage experiences help shape the future of a person it is the experiences in both of these phases of lives which influence a child s future ,7.5
1,The diagram shows the procedure for university entry for high school graduates.Write a report for a university or college lecturer describing the information.,the picture demonstrates the procedure and workflow for university entry for high school graduates in general the whole process for the university application can be divided by three phases including the initial application verification process and subjects selection first of all students who have obtained the high school degree have to complete an application form which can be downloaded from the website of university the completed form can be passed to administration department of university by email or in person around 2 weeks later the student will receive a provisional acceptance issued by administration department to ask for further document submitted in the inital phase the required document must be compiled and sent back to the department within the specified time which is shown on the acceptance a 2 weeks later the rejection notice will be distributed to the ineligible applicant after verified the application with the regarding document the unsucessful applicant can apply for the alternative course and resubmit the completed application form to administration department otherwise the application is regarded as cancellation at the same time the successful applicant will collect an acceptance letter to compete enrolement the eligible applicant will have a registration with the relevant dean after selected subjects after finished the registration the student can enter university ,6.5
