1,"The diagram below shows the life cycle of a salmon, from egg to adult fish.Summarise the information by selecting and reporting the main features and make comparisons where relevant.",the process depicts the steps in which a salmon go through to complete a life cycle overall the whole process is made up by 2 stages each composed of 4 steps from the hatching of the eggs in a river to the maturation in ocean and the migration to spawning area again in a river to begin with the adult salmon spawn and after a period of incubation the newborn salmons emerge and get together in a freshwater rearing as they continue to grow the rearing head off estuary where another nurturing phase takes place looking at the second stage which occurs mainly in the ocean it is noticeable that after the rearing stage in the estuary the salmon s flock undergo a further rearing step in an oceans area necessary to allow them to grow and maturing when the salmons are ripe enough they set out across the estuary toward spawning areas by swimming against the river s stream ,7.0
