1,The diagram below shows how coffee is produced and prepared for sale in supermarkets and shops.Summarise the information by selecting and reporting the main features and make comparisons where relevant.,the diagram illustrates the process with whom coffee is produced and get ready to be sold to food shops overall the process is characterized by 11 phases and needs the help of few workers and machines firstly farmers have to collect the coffee beans from the plants secondly beans need to be dryed through the exposure to the sun and to be roasted by letting them upon the fire thirdly after cooling beans they have to be put in a machine in order to be grinded the next phase leads to a mixture with hot water followed by a straining and freezing one furthermore the resulting frozen liquid has to be grinded again moreover in the next phase the output is collocated in a vacuum which permits the evaporation of the water leading to the last drying part of the process lastly the dryed product is packed into jars with a label and then sold to shops ,6.0
